div.p:
                The firſt, raſh ſwearing, and breaking of their oathes.
2. Sam. 21. Now if we take a generall ſurney of our ſtate, we ſhall find that becauſe of oathes our land ſhall mourne;
Ier. 23.10. for the name of God in no age was ſo blaſphemed either in Iſrael or Iuda, as it is in this ſinfull land. Wee find that many times, they would rent their garments, in hearing the name of God blaſphemed, which if wee ſhould do to heare the Lords name ſo rent and torne in the mouthes of prophane men in ſhops, alehouſes, tauernes, markets, faires, we ſhould neuer haue whole clothes on our backes.
